<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="533" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/995.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Czaykowski</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Cape Haitien</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Zamor Government fallen in the north. Zamor with troops embarked on board
                            Haitian warship for Gonaives. President Zamor believed to be at or going
                            to Gonaives. Revolutionists in Cape. <hi rend="italic">Tacoma’s</hi>
                            forces landed and control foreign district.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. Czaykowski</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>